if not, i feel weak and fatigued through the entire workout. 

try it out and lmk 😉

do the hard shit. 

at the end of last year i couldn’t hit 225lb without a belt

i made it a goal of my to go as up in weight as i can without a belt because through that comes strengthening the core and proper bracing.
i’m not saying don’t wear a belt or that it’s bad to wear a belt. i carry my belt with me all the time just in case i run into that zone where i feel like i need it for heavier lifts. 

do what’s comfortable for you but never too comfortable.

i stopped viewing things as problems and just as situations that need a solution 

life’s been better ever since 💛✨⭐️🌼

✨THINGS KEEPING ME DISCIPLINED LATELY ✨

Wherever you are in life whether that be in a cutting phase, a bulking phase, a figuring it out phase, a ‘alteast I showed up phase’, or simply just trying to live day by day with no desire to be in a different body. 
Discipline is one of those things that makes you feel put together because what you work hard for NO ONE can take away from you.

New lifts, new PR’s, new programs, new friends, new connections and new knowledge, no one can take away what you have worked hard for. 

No. 1: A big reason for my injury was because I was neglecting this part of the gym. It isn’t just pre workout and PR’s, it’s taking care of the muscles and joints that help you get those PR’s. 

No. 2: Staying consistent with your supplements is key. Yes, you hear it all the time but it wouldn’t be said if it wasn’t true. 
@ehplabs oxyshred hardcore and blessed protein have been my key for the summer
helping me with energy and focus and meeting my protein intake

over the course of the last couple months, my relationship with the gym has been rocky. i show up when i can and sometimes the voice in my head tells me how weak I am for not showing up everyday. 

you never know what will come at you next in life so give yourself some grace. 

but that’s just it. 

grace is just the act of being kind to yourself because sometimes things happen that are completely out of your control. 

so, yes be gentle and forgive yourself for not being perfect but dont forget the plan.

why wake up at 5am? 

i hate going to the gym at peak hours so decided to go at 5am.

hint: no it’s not easy

•creating this type of discipline with a morning routine makes you feel unstoppable 
•i’m able to focus better throughout the day 
•more productive with tasks that need to get done
•creates mindfulness with time (helps me with my ADHD) 
•YOU time (no distractions) 

if you wanted to join the 5am club, this is YOUR SIGN.
